===============================================================
FeedFetch - CHANGELOG
===============================================================

Version: 1.2
Date: 2025-10-23
---------------------------------------------------------------
• Added new CONFIGURATION options for improved readability:
  - BULLET_STYLE — adds a prefix before each headline link.
      Example: "• " or "- "  (set to "" for no bullet)
  - LINK_COLOR — sets color of normal (unvisited) links.
  - VISITED_COLOR — sets color of visited links.
• Updated HTML header to include <style> section for link colors.
• Retained plain-text HTML output with no underlines.
• No logic, parsing, or networking behavior changed.
• Fully compatible with prior FeedFetch v1.1 configurations.

---------------------------------------------------------------
Version: 1.1
Date: 2025-10-23
---------------------------------------------------------------
• Simplified output to plain HTML text.
  - Removed all <div>, <ul>, <li>, and CSS box formatting.
  - Headlines now print as <a> links followed by <br>.
• Added CONFIGURATION options:
  - FONT_FAMILY – body text font (e.g. "sans-serif")
  - FONT_SIZE   – font size in pixels (default: 10)
  - BG_COLOR    – page background color (default: #FFFFFF)
• Adjusted HTML wrapper to apply only body-level styling.
• Links now appear as plain text:
  - Added inline style "text-decoration:none; color:inherit"
  - Removes underlines and color highlighting.
• Maintained all networking, decoding, and parsing logic:
  - HTTPS (via IO::Socket::SSL)
  - Chunked, gzip, and deflate decoding
  - RSS / Atom / RDF parsing
  - Multi-level redirect handling
• Debugging system unchanged (enable with DEBUG='Y' or ?debug=1)
• Fully compatible with FeedServ v1.0 front-end layouts.

---------------------------------------------------------------
Version: 1.0
Date: 2025-10-22
---------------------------------------------------------------
• Initial stable modular release.
• Added subroutine-based structure:
  - fetch_with_fallback()
  - fetch_http()
  - decode_chunked(), decode_gzip(), decode_deflate()
  - parse_rss(), parse_atom(), parse_rdf()
• Added robust header/body split and decoding sequence.
• Implemented graceful HTTP/HTTPS fallback.
• Added DEBUG mode (runtime or query-string toggle).
• Verified compatibility with multiple public feeds.
• First version to properly handle gzip and chunked feeds.
• Formatted output in graphical boxes (now deprecated).

===============================================================
End of CHANGELOG
===============================================================
